<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="properly-adv">properly <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'prɒpəli/    美 /'prɑːpərli/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-right">1.★ <strong>正确地；适当地；恰当地 (right)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She thinks that children must eat properly as they are growing all the time.
她认为儿童必须合理饮食，因为他们正处于生长发育阶段。</p><footer>译林① – 3</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>合乎礼仪地：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>behave properly 
举止得体</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>真正地；实际上；严格地：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>properly speaking</strong> (= really)
严格说来 / 实际上</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>A dog's eating habit requires regular training before it is <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (proper) established.  （2019 天津改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. properly  </p></div>